<br>
Officers:  these are the lowest ranking members able to recruit (i.e., add new members).  So to qualify to become an officer, you need to be some-one that we can trust to discern good players and try to recruit them.  If you have been lucky and grouped with one of the Guildmasters or elders a lot, it may only take a few weeks for you to be promoted (my aplogies to guildies that went un-promoted for so long in the past).  There is no quota on &quot;members per week&quot; or some such for officers.  We would rather add one good player a month  then six idgits a week (Alayn heard that quip first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    ).  <br>
<br>
Elders: these are the lowest ranking members that are able to boot members and make promotions.  To become an elder you need to have been in the guild for a long time.  You also need to have played with Salt or I enough that we know that your play style is pretty similar to ours.  It also helps a lot if you are on more then we are.  An Elder needs to be on when we are not around, and keep track of guildies that are distruptive.  An Elder is basically someone with a &quot;license to boot.&quot;  And, during random periods when Salt and I have not been able to play much (we are both geezers with real jobs, I am often out of town for weeks at a time) also we expect Elders to promote officers from the ranks of new recruits.  Just like with new members, there is no quota on new officers.  <br>
<br>
Guildmasters: We determine overall guild strategy.  We also make web sites that no-one looks at <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     When we are on, we will settle disputes about promotions, take petitions for readmission to the guild, and promote/ demote.   If you have any concerns about the guild, Send Gamkak or Salt a mail in game.  The next time we happen to log, the problem will get fixed immediatly.  The two things we most want to hear about:<br>
<br>
1. If you think you have been passed over for promotion unfairly.<br>
<br>
2. If there is a guildy you have a gripe with.<br>
<br>
From now on I am going to be a lot less hesitent to promote/ use my boot stick and I presume that Salt feels the same way. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bknightsofnorrath91133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grizlith>Grizlith</A> at: 5/11/03 5:20:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bknightsofnorrath91133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salt@knightsofnorrath91133>Salt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#939393>(5/12/03 8:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub27.ezboard.com/fknightsofnorrath91133frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thoughts on Promotions</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>From now on I am going to be a lot less hesitent to promote/ use my boot stick and I presume that Salt feels the same way.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Salt feels exactly the same way.  Even though the guild is smaller now, I really enjoy knowing that when I login, the only people in the guild are people that I enjoy playing with.  I don't even have to wonder 'gee, i hope so and so will be on today', because when I login, _everyone_ is someone I wouldn't mind playing with.<br>
<br>
The only challenge will be trying to keep the guild in that state.  (Which is why we will reward those who are cool players, and boot those aren't.)<br>
<br>
One important thing to me is that I will boot anyone who pulls a train on another group of characters, or who others find even slightly offensive.  This may seem harsh to some, but I think that everyone else will be happy to have such individuals in some _other_ guild.<br>
<br>
I just want to reiterate that the members in our guild today are awesome players!  Anyone who is an officer should feel free to invite their friends into the guild, and you don't need to ask any of the elders'/guildmasters' permission.  If you guys have fun playing with someone else, then chances are others in the guild will have fun playing with them too.<br>
<br>
